<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 93 / Rome's ex-envoy to US probed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Anti-corruption investigators yesterday ordered the arrest of Mr Rinaldo
Petrignani, a former Italian ambassador to Washington, as part of Italy's
corruption scandal, judicial sources said, Reuter reports from Milan. The
sources said Mr Petrignani, 65, was wanted for questioning about the role he
played as an adviser to US merchant bank Salomon Brothers after leaving the
Washington embassy, his last diplomatic post, in 1991. Mr Petrignani was
quoted as saying in Washington he was sure the matter would be cleared up
very shortly.
