FT  28 OCT 93 / Anti-EC group forms in Norway
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN FOSSLI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   OSLO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A faction of Norway's ruling Labour party yesterday announced it had formed
an organisation to keep Norway out of the European Community, writes Karen
Fossli from Oslo. The new organisation, called Social Democrats against the
EC, said it would seek to strengthen the domestic anti-EC movement so that a
referendum on membership, to be held by 1996, would reject the move. Mrs Gro
Harlem Brundtland, Norway's prime minister, refused to comment on the
announcement, as did Mr Torbjoern Jagland, the leader of the Labour party.
