<TEXT>
Greece has recalled its ambassador to Tirana following violent clashes last
week in a southern Albanian village, where an elderly woman from the ethnic
Greek minority reportedly died of injuries resulting from a beating by
Albanian police, writes Kerin Hope from Athens. The Albanian government
