FT  28 OCT 93 / Moscow urges peacekeeping help
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTHONY ROBINSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Andrei Kozyrev, the Russian foreign minister, yesterday called on the
west to help Russia sustain difficult and expensive peacekeeping operations
to prevent the former Soviet Union drifting into what he called a 'Yugoslav
scenario', writes Anthony Robinson.
Instead of criticising Russia's actions as neo-imperialist, 'we consider it
high time to seriously consider the possibility of sharing this peacekeeping
burden with Russia,' he said in a speech at London's Royal Institute of
International Affairs.
