   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission has given Germany two months to abolish tax aid to
its national airlines on the grounds that it distorts competition in the EC
aviation market, Reuter reports from Brussels. Brussels said Bonn had two
months to say whether it would abolish by next January the scheme which
allows its airlines to pay less tax by applying special depreciation rules
to their investments. The scheme is due to finish at the end of next year.
