FT  27 OCT 93 / International Company News: Hoogovens in talks to sell six
units
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HOOGOVENS, the Dutch metals group, is negotiating the sale of six small
companies representing half its industrial supply division, as part of plans
to concentrate on its main steel and aluminium businesses.
The six companies, with combined annual sales of Fl 250m (Dollars 138m) and
a workforce of 1,000 people, are to be sold as a group to three Dutch
venture capital companies - Albif, Alpinvest and Nederlandse Participatie
Maatschappij.
The rest of the companies in the industrial supply division are to be
distributed among Hoogovens' other four divisions but they may be sold later
if buyers can be found.
Hoogovens, which is struggling to reduce losses and debts, announced this
year that it planned to start divesting non-core businesses.
The six companies are Bihca Precision, Gieterij Nunspeet, Nederlandse
Draadindustrie, Achilles, Thibo Draad and El-o-Matic Holding, in which
Hoogovens owns a 46.6 per cent stake.
