125m to help reduce its net debt. It stood at Pounds 1.9bn for gearing of 84
per cent at last December but it had been cut to around 70 per cent in
September.
The sale would raise funds at a time when cash generation by its other
operations was being hampered by recession.
P&amp;O said Laing Properties Inc would continue to own some 2.7m sq ft of
commercial property, which was part of the dealing portfolio.
