<HEADLINE>
FT  27 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Bradford Property at Pounds 17.5m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SALE of land near Ipswich for a Tesco superstore helped Bradford
Property Trust, the UK's largest tenanted residential property company, to
lift pre-tax profits by more than 50 per cent, from Pounds 11.6m to Pounds
17.5m, for the six months to October 5.
Yesterday the shares closed 8p ahead at 226p.
The surplus from property rentals increased by almost 21 per cent from
Pounds 5.3m to Pounds 6.4m. Dealing profits rose from Pounds 6.2m to Pounds
11.4m following the Ipswich land sale. Total operating profit was Pounds
17.8m (Pounds 11.5m).
Interest payable increased from Pounds 545,000 to Pounds 641,000.
The interim dividend, based on the surplus from property rentals after tax
and preference dividends, rose from 2.4p to 2.9p. Earnings per share were up
from 5.43p to 8.11p.
The company's business centres on buying tenanted properties at a discount
to reflect the statutory rights of sitting tenants and selling them with
vacant possession.
