FT  27 OCT 93 / The Lex Column: Ferranti
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In retrospect, Ferranti's fate was sealed when it signed the deal with
International Signal in 1987, though the end of the cold war and low oil
prices have delivered the coup de grace. So why should anyone be prepared to
take on the company's substantial debts at this stage? There are some
businesses within Ferranti which are worth having - notably the naval sonar
operation. That is worse than buying a shop to get a can of baked beans.
Perhaps GEC or Thomson might wish to curry favour with the Ministry of
Defence by rescuing one of its contractors, which looks like an expensive
favour unless Ferranti's tax losses or pension fund surplus can be made to
work for the bidder.
