<HEADLINE>
FT  27 OCT 93 / EC joins US in push on services
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GEORGE GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE European Community is to join the US push to make Asian and Latin
American countries open their financial services markets more widely as the
Uruguay Round of trade liberalisation talks comes to a climax.
Mr Lawrence Summers, the US Treasury undersecretary in charge of
international affairs, said yesterday the EC had agreed to follow the US
example by sending high-level officials to several emerging markets in an
effort to 'help unblock the Geneva logjam.'
Mr Summers said the Clinton administration's decision to back legislation
authorising restrictions on the expansion of banks and financial service
companies from countries which do not allow equal access to US businesses
would serve as a lever to secure additional concessions in the sector before
the conclusion of the Uruguay round.
'The offers from many of the participants in the negotiations are simply not
good enough,' he said.
