<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 93 / London Stock Exchange: Scotia strong
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Another stock launching into the market yesterday was Scotia Holdings, the
research-based pharmaceuticals group that has financed its growth from
products based on evening primrose oil.
Strong institutional demand for the shares pushed turnover up to 5.5m. The
issue was placed at 290p and immediately jumped to a strong premium at 323p.
Some profit-taking then set in and took the shine off, with the shares
closing at 316p.
Dealers said bullish sentiment surrounds the stock and its strong start is
not expected to peter out. One analyst said: 'It has been an excellent
debut, with institutions waiting to mop up the shares.'
